1 + 2 + 3","distance_km":null,"result_count":2,"control_count":null,"course_climb_m":null}],"event_id":"019b81b3-75e2-7310-b1d6-3ff2df7cff57","venue_id":"019b81b3-75d3-76e5-a365-d9446ba1ba40","event_date":"2004-06-12","event_kind":"race","event_name":"Rattlesnake Lake","venue_name":"Rattlesnake Lake","event_notes":null,"course_count":4,"event_status":null,"result_count":36,"citation_count":2,"event_comments":"About 50 newcomers joined us at Rattlesnake Lake on Mountains to Sound Greenway Discovery Days. It seems that most of them learned about the event through the Discovery Days publicity. A few regulars came, also, to check out the new map completed by Mike Schuh and Eric Bone. The park was quite busy; there was also a multi-sport race that involved at least paddling and biking, and several participants thought our registration table was a race checkpoint. A few casual passers-by decided to do a course, and one Swedish-American fellow stopped in just to pick up a Cascade event schedule.\nEric Bone set up the event with the Discovery Days people and set the courses. Many thanks to Mike Schuh for clinics and to Libby & Don Dermenstein for registration, start, and finish. We look forward to having more meets in this beautiful lakeside green space.","external_links":[],"volunteer_roles":[{"role_name":"Clinics","individual_id":"0191394f-d748-7189-887f-793488143b6d","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Mike Schuh","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Course Setter","individual_id":"019b7acf-182c-7c41-bf38-2f166390b465","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Eric Bone","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Registration/Start/Finish","individual_id":"019b9a64-8016-79a1-95d1-f9a393d6ab58","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Don Dermenstein","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Registration/Start/Finish","individual_id":"019b9a64-8016-737d-acb2-1a7c0ff6f1ee","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Libby Dermenstein","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null}],"organizing_club_id":"01912f3e-e3e1-7e8e-b3c6-32387a8b4990","result_source_brief":"Older COC Results Website: http://www.old.cascadeoc.org/Results2004/rattlesnake.html","organizing_club_name":"Cascade Orienteering Club","cumulative_event_comments":"About 50 newcomers joined us at Rattlesnake Lake on Mountains to Sound Greenway Discovery Days. It seems that most of them learned about the event through the Discovery Days publicity. A few regulars came, also, to check out the new map completed by Mike Schuh and Eric Bone. The park was quite busy; there was also a multi-sport race that involved at least paddling and biking, and several participants thought our registration table was a race checkpoint. A few casual passers-by decided to do a course, and one Swedish-American fellow stopped in just to pick up a Cascade event schedule.\nEric Bone set up the event with the Discovery Days people and set the courses. Many thanks to Mike Schuh for clinics and to Libby & Don Dermenstein for registration, start, and finish. We look forward to having more meets in this beautiful lakeside green space."}
